{
  "answer": "**Manusmṛti 1.91** states the following about the duty of the Shudra:\n\n> But the one duty the Lord assigned to the Shudra was to serve these other *varnas* without malice.[^1]\n\nThis verse occurs in the context of the creation of the four *varnas* (social orders): Brahmana from the mouth, Kshatriya from the arms, Vaishya from the thighs, and Shudra from the feet. It specifies service to the other three *varnas* (*adhitriṇān*) as the singular obligation assigned by the creator.[^2]\n\n[^1]: Manusmṛti, Chapter 1, [paragraph](/works/unknown-manusmrti-347b76/01/translation/#p-26a572).\n[^2]: Manusmṛti, Chapter 1, [paragraph](/works/unknown-manusmrti-347b76/01/translation/#p-13a2db).",
